-- Dubai Investments Second-Quarter Profit Drops 32% as Property Income Falls
-- Arif Sharif
-- 2010-07-28T13:37:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/dubai-investments-second-quarter-profit-drops-32-as-property-income-falls.html

          
          
             Dubai Investments PJSC , which owns
stakes in more than 40 companies, reported a 32 percent decline
in second-quarter profit as investment income dropped.  
 Net income fell to 196.3 million dirhams ($53 million) from
287 million dirhams a year earlier, the company said in a
statement to the Dubai bourse today. Income from sale of goods
and services fell 1.8 percent 309.4 million dirhams, while
contract revenue rose 30 percent to 213.8 million dirhams.  
 Dubai Investments wrote down the value of its investments
by 49.7 million dirhams in the quarter, while it had a profit of
53 million dirhams a year ago, the results showed.  
 Dubai Investments  shares  rose 0.6 percent to close at 83.9
fils on the Dubai bourse before the results were announced. The
shares have fallen 16 percent this year, valuing the company at
3 billion dirhams.  
